WEBVTT

00:04.325 --> 00:06.747
Previously, on the Truth About
the Harry Quebert Affair...

00:06.847 --> 00:08.469
I told you, Bobbo.

00:08.569 --> 00:10.551
Harry Quebert is taking
Jenny to Augusta

00:10.651 --> 00:11.552
to see the fireworks.

00:11.652 --> 00:13.153
Who's Harry Quebert?

00:13.253 --> 00:14.675
Mom, I don't think
he's coming.

00:14.775 --> 00:16.196
Who the hell is
getting married?

00:16.296 --> 00:17.597
Excuse me.

00:17.697 --> 00:18.838
Tell us already.

00:18.938 --> 00:21.361
What are we supposed
to be celebrating?

00:21.461 --> 00:22.762
Um...

00:22.862 --> 00:24.684
My dear friends,

00:24.784 --> 00:26.766
we have a new color television.

00:26.866 --> 00:28.888
Robert has cancer.

00:28.988 --> 00:30.449
-What?
-Here's to Bobbo.

00:30.549 --> 00:33.272
Oh, you
poor thing.

00:35.954 --> 00:37.616
[Jenny yelps in fright]
Oh, my God!

00:37.716 --> 00:39.057
Luther, you scared me! Geez!

00:39.157 --> 00:40.618
What does he want
from you?

00:40.718 --> 00:42.660
He's a friend.
Ow, you're hurting me.

00:42.760 --> 00:44.302
Did somebody do that
to you, Jenny?

00:44.402 --> 00:47.685
You know Luther Caleb,
Stern's chauffeur?

00:49.166 --> 00:51.468
<i>[Elijah Stern]: I had hoped</i>
<i>that Nola would be the last,</i>

00:51.568 --> 00:52.990
<i>that he would paint her</i>

00:53.090 --> 00:55.512
<i>and get whatever it was</i>
<i>out of his system.</i>

00:55.612 --> 00:57.914
So you think it was Luther
who killed Nola?

00:58.014 --> 01:00.897
I've thought so
for the last 33 years.

01:02.578 --> 01:03.920
Is this Luther's handwriting?

01:04.020 --> 01:06.202
His instructions
for pruning roses.

01:06.302 --> 01:09.004
You can keep it
if it'll help you.

01:09.104 --> 01:11.927
Nola's home life
was not a happy one.

01:12.027 --> 01:13.849
Nola, is somebody beating you?

01:13.949 --> 01:15.330
It's my mom.

01:15.430 --> 01:17.612
She says
I'm a wicked girl.

01:17.712 --> 01:18.533
That's crazy.

01:18.633 --> 01:20.635
My mother told me
I had to be punished.

01:23.157 --> 01:24.218
[gasping]

01:24.318 --> 01:26.220
Take a look at that.

01:26.320 --> 01:28.462
"Nola, my darling,

01:28.562 --> 01:31.665
were you to die,
where would my love go?"

01:31.765 --> 01:33.767
Keep it in your safe for now.

01:34.568 --> 01:36.570
[scoffs]

01:37.971 --> 01:40.433
[whispering] You're gonna
be a great writer,

01:40.533 --> 01:43.356
and we're gonna get
a big sun-colored dog,

01:43.456 --> 01:46.279
a Labrador we'll name Storm.

01:46.379 --> 01:48.481
<i>The big news out of the State</i>
<i>courthouse this morning</i>

01:48.581 --> 01:50.923
<i>is that Harry Quebert</i>
<i>is being released on bail</i>

01:51.023 --> 01:52.284
<i>due to lack of evidence.</i>

01:52.384 --> 01:54.126
[Roth]: The handwriting
isn't Harry's.

01:54.226 --> 01:57.088
He didn't write the note
on that goddamn manuscript.

01:57.189 --> 01:58.890
Gareth is staying
at the Montburry Motel

01:58.990 --> 02:00.572
since his release.

02:00.672 --> 02:02.053
They informed everyone in town

02:02.153 --> 02:04.655
there's a registered
sex offender in their midst.

02:04.755 --> 02:06.297
Pratt found
the black Monte Carlo,

02:06.397 --> 02:07.578
then he dismissed it?

02:07.678 --> 02:09.540
I'll call the station,
find out where he is.

02:09.640 --> 02:11.642
No, actually,
I already know.

02:13.043 --> 02:14.064
Pratt, open up!

02:14.164 --> 02:15.465
[kicking door]

02:15.565 --> 02:17.567
Shit!

