that now he'd talk.

04:04.265 --> 04:06.647
With everybody knowing
what he did to Nola,

04:06.747 --> 04:08.249
he knew he had nothing to lose.

04:08.349 --> 04:09.650
Yeah, except his life.

04:09.750 --> 04:11.211
Yeah, except that.

04:11.311 --> 04:13.674
You have a theory?

04:14.795 --> 04:18.038
I keep coming back
to Elijah Stern.

04:19.919 --> 04:22.662
<i>What if Stern got home</i>
<i>from meetings that day,</i>

04:22.762 --> 04:26.025
<i>August 30th, like he said.</i>

04:26.125 --> 04:30.829
<i>He finds Luther gone,</i>
<i>and so is the Monte Carlo.</i>

04:30.929 --> 04:33.832
<i>Maybe he hears on the radio</i>
<i>that Nola is missing,</i>

04:33.932 --> 04:36.635
<i>and that sends him out</i>
<i>searching for Luther,</i>

04:36.735 --> 04:38.877
<i>worried he's mixed up in it...</i>

04:38.977 --> 04:40.798
[power window whines]

04:40.899 --> 04:42.320
Evening, Officer.

04:42.420 --> 04:44.041
-Evening.
-What's going on?

04:44.141 --> 04:46.604
Well, we got reports
of a missing girl in the area,

04:46.704 --> 04:48.205
so we're asking people
to stay off the roads

04:48.305 --> 04:49.486
until we find her.

04:49.586 --> 04:50.728
Missing girl?

04:50.828 --> 04:51.889
Where are you
headed tonight?

04:51.989 --> 04:53.730
Uh, I was just
on my way home,

04:53.830 --> 04:55.892
but I'm sure
I can find another way.

04:55.992 --> 04:56.893
We'd appreciate that, sir,

04:56.993 --> 04:58.254
if you don't mind
turning around.

04:58.355 --> 04:59.456
Have a good night.

04:59.556 --> 05:01.557
You too.

05:02.158 --> 05:05.141
<i>[Perry continues]: But</i>
<i>maybe instead of going home,</i>

05:05.241 --> 05:07.243
<i>Stern drove to Goose Cove.</i>

05:24.619 --> 05:26.080
<i>Maybe he finds Luther there,</i>

05:26.180 --> 05:29.523
<i>who confesses to killing</i>
<i>Deborah Cooper as well...</i>

05:29.623 --> 05:30.884
[breathing hard]
Please help me.

05:30.984 --> 05:34.628
Get a shovel and a pickaxe
from the shed.

05:35.869 --> 05:37.851
<i>[Perry]: Luther tended</i>
<i>the grounds at Goose Cove,</i>

05:37.951 --> 05:41.734
<i>so it makes sense that</i>
<i>they would bury Nola there.</i>

05:41.834 --> 05:43.176
<i>After they dig the grave,</i>

05:43.276 --> 05:44.897
<i>Luther could've</i>
<i>secretly written</i>

05:44.997 --> 05:47.119
<i>the farewell note to Nola.</i>

05:54.046 --> 05:55.187
After that,

05:55.287 --> 05:56.948
Stern needs to find
a way to protect Luther,

05:57.048 --> 05:57.989
and that way is Pratt.

05:58.089 --> 06:00.552
Pratt?

06:00.652 --> 06:02.193
Let's say Luther
saw Pratt grab Nola,

06:02.293 --> 06:04.355
pull her into his car.

06:04.455 --> 06:06.997
You know, Luther had been
watching her like a hawk.

06:07.098 --> 06:08.999
Let's say he told Stern.
-Mm-hmm.

06:09.099 --> 06:11.281
Stern goes to see Pratt.

06:11.381 --> 06:13.964
He tells him, "You let Luther
get out of town clean,

06:14.064 --> 06:16.146
and I'll let you get away with
what you did to that girl."

06:17.867 --> 06:20.290
<i>But even if Pratt lets him</i>
<i>get away with the murder,</i>

06:20.390 --> 06:23.332
<i>maybe Luther can't live</i>
<i>with what he did.</i>

06:23.432 --> 06:24.894
[Luther]: I'm so sorry, Eli.

06:24.994 --> 06:26.996
[car engine starts]

06:30.039 --> 06:31.780
<i>He commits suicide</i>
<i>a few days later</i>

06:31.880 --> 06:33.882
<i>by driving his car off a cliff.</i>

06:40.208 --> 06:41.829
And the weirdest part
in all this, though...

06:41.929 --> 06:44.392
why would Stern go
through all this mess,

06:44.492 --> 06:46.353
I mean, maybe even
kill someone,

06:46.454 --> 06:48.455
to protect Luther?

06:50.858 --> 06:53.920
Still trying
to figure that part out.

06:54.021 --> 06:56.743
[distant thunder rumbles]

07:09.074 --> 07:11.076
[car door closes]

07:13.719 --> 07:16.421
They're burying her today,
aren't they?

07:16.521 --> 07:19.023
Yeah.

07:19.124 --> 07:22.847
They're burying her,
and I'm not there.

07:25.730 --> 07:28.953
[groaning]

07:29.053 --> 07:31.054
Ah, I wish I was dead.

07:35.779 --> 07:40.363
And may she rest
in eternal peace.

