and he would say,
"This is insane.

36:10.910 --> 36:12.212
This is insane!"

36:12.312 --> 36:13.973
[laughing]

36:14.073 --> 36:16.075
You do say that a lot.

36:16.916 --> 36:18.918
[clerk shouts]
Go around!

36:22.761 --> 36:24.763
Can I see it?

36:39.737 --> 36:40.878
"Dear Marcus,

36:40.978 --> 36:42.199
if you're still
looking for answers,

36:42.299 --> 36:43.240
this may interest you.

36:43.340 --> 36:44.241
This book is the truth.

36:44.341 --> 36:46.343
Harry."

36:48.064 --> 36:50.887
<i>"The Seagulls of Sommerdale"</i>
by Harry L. Quebert.

36:50.987 --> 36:54.210
It's an unpublished
book of Harry's.

36:54.310 --> 36:55.471
I don't know, he always said
Nola loved seagulls.

36:55.551 --> 36:56.852
There must be some connection.

36:56.953 --> 36:58.954
But what does that mean,
"This book is the truth"?

37:05.961 --> 37:08.483
Oh, man, this ending.

37:11.126 --> 37:12.467
He and Nola,

37:12.567 --> 37:15.409
living happily
ever after?

37:17.571 --> 37:18.713
Hmm.

37:18.813 --> 37:21.635
I guess he made it
to writer's heaven.

37:21.735 --> 37:23.517
What's that?

37:23.617 --> 37:25.279
It's like when you, um...

37:25.379 --> 37:26.400
you get to see your life

37:26.500 --> 37:28.522
the way you wish
you'd lived it.

37:28.622 --> 37:30.523
I guess you, uh...

37:30.623 --> 37:32.625
write your way to being happy.

37:35.748 --> 37:38.931
So what do you think
he's trying to tell you now?

37:39.031 --> 37:41.393
"This book is the truth."

37:43.195 --> 37:45.557
I have no fucking idea.

37:49.240 --> 37:50.622
I don't know,
maybe you could try

37:50.722 --> 37:53.264
telling us the truth this time.

37:53.364 --> 37:54.625
I don't know what
you're implying, Mr. Goldman.

37:54.726 --> 37:56.067
You came here
asking me questions,

37:56.167 --> 37:57.508
and I answered them
to the best of my ability.

37:57.608 --> 37:59.150
You told me Nola's mother
was beating her, and...

37:59.250 --> 38:00.431
[cell phone rings]

38:00.531 --> 38:02.112
and how shocked you were
when she told you--

38:02.212 --> 38:03.834
No, what I actually said,

38:03.934 --> 38:05.435
and you can check your notes,

38:05.535 --> 38:07.757
is that Nola told me
her mother beat her.

38:07.858 --> 38:10.080
And yes, that was shocking,
considering the fact

38:10.180 --> 38:11.841
that her mother had been dead
for nine years.

38:11.941 --> 38:13.242
[laughs in disbelief]

38:13.343 --> 38:14.564
Uh...

38:14.664 --> 38:15.925
you never said anything
about her being dead.

38:16.025 --> 38:17.727
I assumed you knew.

38:17.827 --> 38:19.528
Everybody knew that.

38:19.628 --> 38:21.050
How could you not know,

38:21.150 --> 38:23.152
famous writer
from New York and all?

38:24.673 --> 38:26.675
[sighing] Oh, God...

38:27.435 --> 38:31.399
I... I honestly didn't mean
to mislead you.

38:34.602 --> 38:36.604
Okay.

38:38.806 --> 38:39.987
[sighs]

38:40.087 --> 38:42.589
Got the name of the old kook
who went after Harry.

38:42.689 --> 38:45.652
I'm sure he'll be thrilled
to see you.

38:56.182 --> 38:58.184
[moaning]

39:02.307 --> 39:04.810
[panting and seething]

39:04.910 --> 39:08.373
You're not welcome here,
Mr. Goldman.

39:08.473 --> 39:12.497
You desecrated the memory
of my wife and daughter!

39:12.597 --> 39:13.418
All right.

39:13.518 --> 39:14.158
Just please put
the gun down,

39:14.238 --> 39:15.540
Mr. Kellergan.

39:15.640 --> 39:17.501
Why did you threaten Harry
at the By The Sea Motel?

39:17.601 --> 39:21.525
Because he's still alive,
and my daughter's dead!

39:25.649 --> 39:26.630
[rifle cracks]

39:26.730 --> 39:28.592
All right,
all right, hey!

39:28.692 --> 39:29.592
That's enough,
Reverend!

39:29.693 --> 39:31.114
Give me the rifle!

39:31.214 --> 39:33.636
[seething] I ought to sue you
for every penny you got.

39:33.736 --> 39:35.198
I ought to sue you

39:35.298 --> 39:36.759
for that trash you wrote.

39:36.859 --> 39:37.780
And why haven't you
done that already?

39:37.860 --> 39:38.841
I'll take everything
that you've got!

39:38.941 --> 39:39.782
Why haven't you
done that already?

39:39.862 --> 39:40.603
Writer!

39:40.703 --> 39:41.643
Huh? No,
no, no. No!

39:41.744 --> 39:42.644
Why aren't we
in court

39:42.744 --> 39:43.846
right now?
-[police siren wails]

39:43.946 --> 39:46.028
Maybe it's because
you're the one you beat Nola!

39:47.869 --> 39:50.131
I never laid a hand
on my daughter!

39:50.231 --> 39:51.172
Or maybe
it's just because

39:51.272 --> 39:51.873
you don't want people
finding out

39:51.953 --> 39:53.334
what happened in Alabama.

39:53.434 --> 39:54.655
[Travis]: Okay, okay.

39:54.756 --> 39:56.457
Okay, Reverend,
let's not lose our cool here.

39:56.557 --> 39:57.618
Put down the gun.

39:57.718 --> 39:59.059
And we are
going to find out!

39:59.160 --> 40:00.621
[moaning] You are a devil.

40:00.721 --> 40:02.623
You're a devil.

40:02.723 --> 40:05.065
[sobbing] God...

40:05.165 --> 40:07.667
Sorry about the
disturbance, Chief.

40:07.767 --> 40:10.450
We'll be on our way.

40:13.333 --> 40:14.794
[airplane engines roar]

40:14.894 --> 40:16.155
Thanks for doing this.

40:16.255 --> 40:17.236
Really appreciate it.

40:17.336 --> 40:18.757
Oh, happy to help.

40:18.858 --> 40:19.798
Here.

40:19.899 --> 40:22.361
Thought you might
find this interesting.

40:22.461 --> 40:25.203
David Kellergan married
Louisa Bonneville

40:25.303 --> 40:27.205
in 1955,

40:27.305 --> 40:28.486
and became a pastor

40:28.587 --> 40:30.568
in the parish
of Mount Pleasant.

40:30.668 --> 40:33.291
Five years later,
Nola was born.

40:33.391 --> 40:34.452
To everybody,

40:34.552 --> 40:35.653
they seemed like
the perfect

40:35.753 --> 40:38.676
God-fearing
Alabama family...

40:40.678 --> 40:43.320
until the tragedy in 1966.

40:46.603 --> 40:48.825
What tragedy?

40:48.925 --> 40:50.707
The Reverend came home
at 2:00 a.m.

40:50.807 --> 40:53.109
<i>after spending the evening</i>

40:53.209 --> 40:55.211
<i>at a dying parishioner's</i>
<i>bedside.</i>

41:00.215 --> 41:02.498
Louisa! Oh, God!

41:10.185 --> 41:12.186
[gasping]

41:14.188 --> 41:15.530
[winces in pain] Ah!

41:15.630 --> 41:17.631
[wood splintering]

41:18.993 --> 41:20.995
Louisa!

41:23.597 --> 41:25.599
Nola!

41:41.533 --> 41:42.915
<i>[Officer]: His wife was found</i>
<i>burned to death,</i>

41:43.015 --> 41:44.836
<i>but his daughter survived.</i>

41:44.936 --> 41:47.479
The tragedy occurred
on August 30th.

41:47.579 --> 41:49.080
Holy shit!

41:49.180 --> 41:51.523
Nola disappeared
nine years later to the day.

41:51.623 --> 41:54.685
For a long time after,
there was some talk.

41:54.785 --> 41:55.726
I mean, the pastor
just so happens

41:55.826 --> 41:57.728
to show up in time
to save his daughter,

41:57.828 --> 41:59.830
but not his wife.

42:01.392 --> 42:05.095
Seems fishy, but they had
no evidence against him.

42:05.195 --> 42:07.717
[door closes,
car engine starts]

42:12.562 --> 42:14.564
[car engine turns off]

42:20.809 --> 42:22.751
Pastor Lewis worked
at a neighboring parish.

42:22.851 --> 42:24.793
He was a good friend
of the Kellergans.

42:24.893 --> 42:26.154
You'll see,

42:26.254 --> 42:29.377
he's still pretty sprightly
for a 90-year-old.

42:32.180 --> 42:35.883
[Pastor Lewis]:
I have never known...

42:35.983 --> 42:39.607
a family...

42:39.707 --> 42:41.568
as happy...

42:41.668 --> 42:43.670
as that one.

42:51.838 --> 42:54.780
David and Louisa,

42:54.881 --> 42:56.942
they were made by the Lord

42:57.043 --> 42:59.164
to love one another.

43:01.847 --> 43:03.709
And Nola,

43:03.809 --> 43:05.791
my...

43:05.891 --> 43:07.953
She was...

43:08.053 --> 43:10.955
an extraordinary,

43:11.055 --> 43:13.738
beautiful little girl.

43:19.223 --> 43:23.867
It gave you
undying hope in humanity.

43:27.070 --> 43:30.934
Until one day...

43:31.034 --> 43:32.815
[beeps remote]

43:32.915 --> 43:34.917
[mechanism whirring]

43:36.519 --> 43:40.082
...we exorcised her.

43:52.774 --> 43:54.675
But...

43:54.775 --> 43:58.879
it didn't go as planned.

43:58.979 --> 44:00.240
Uh...

44:00.341 --> 44:02.402
you exorcised who?

44:02.503 --> 44:07.887
Nola, the little girl.

44:07.988 --> 44:12.091
That girl
had so much evil in her.

44:12.191 --> 44:15.895
The devil's claws
were stuck deep in her heart,

44:15.995 --> 44:20.439
into the depths of her soul.

44:21.880 --> 44:24.903
<i>The night of the fire</i>
<i>did not go</i>

44:25.003 --> 44:29.988
<i>quite the way David Kellergan</i>
<i>told the police.</i>

44:30.088 --> 44:31.589
Nola!

44:31.689 --> 44:32.910
Louisa!

44:33.010 --> 44:34.031
Oh, God!

44:34.132 --> 44:36.133
[gasping]

44:41.618 --> 44:43.080
[wincing in pain] Ah!

44:43.180 --> 44:45.182
[wood splintering]

44:49.546 --> 44:51.547
Nola...

44:52.148 --> 44:53.850
Nola?

44:53.950 --> 44:56.012
Nola! Nola!

44:56.112 --> 44:57.893
[coughing] Nola!

